"My greatest secret would not be published," says a decade-year-old Jorge in trying to explain the importance of privacy in sites such as Facebook, Twitter, Hotmail and Windows Live Messenger, where he has accounts for two years.
"They are very secret secrets, my mom can know about them, but not the whole world," she says.
"I'm putting nice pictures or photos on the FB as we play.
